title: *PATREON PREVIEW* Touching Wood Pt. II with Angelo Urrutia
description:
The IYKYK drum beats on behind the paywall for the Patreon-exclusive part 2 of Throwing Fits’ interview with your favorite designer’s favorite designer, Angelo Urrutia. Angelo and the boys are getting into the carne y papas to talk hustling and fighting as a wayward youth, bagging good girls, power ranking the 5 boroughs, dropping out of art school, Rainbow Sandals as jawnz, the legend of Daiki Suzuki, EG biters and culture vultures, when good collabs go bad, Japanese personal style, the joy of people watching, the 4SDesigns elevator pitch, the luxury of time, learning to put yourself out there, the sport of competitive capping, jewelry and fragrance ambitions, and much more.
 
For more Throwing Fits, check us out on Patreon: www.patreon.com/throwingfits
